    "text":  "COO Mom. who\u0027s For breakfast? WAKE THE You grow up so fast! But here\u0027s what happened after you were born. Female hummingbirds usually lay two white eggs about the size of small jelly beans Your mom sat on her eggs for two or three weeks before they hatched. You probably hatched in late spring or early summer. depending on where you live. Your mom is an amazing architect! When building your nest. she used spider silk-the strong. elastic fiber spiders produce to catch prey. the silk stretched as you grew. so your home was the perfect size. Baby hummingbirds are called clicks. hatchmgs. or nesdings You didn\u0027t open your eyes or start growing any feathers until about nine days after you hatched You stayed pretty quiet as a baby-except when you were really hungry When you were small. your mom fed you small bugs and nectar from her bill. You spent about three weeks in your mom\u0027s nest before you were big enough to fly and live on your own. Every year. you like to retum to the same place you were born.",
